class Solution:
    def leafSimilar(self, root1: Optional[TreeNode], root2: Optional[TreeNode]) -> bool:

        def get_leaf_sequence(node):
            if not node:
                return []
            if not node.left and not node.right:
                return [node.val]
            return get_leaf_sequence(node.left) + get_leaf_sequence(node.right)

        return get_leaf_sequence(root1) == get_leaf_sequence(root2)
```

This solution defines a helper function `get_leaf_sequence` that performs a depth-first search (DFS) on the tree to collect all leaf node values in a list. The `leafSimilar` method then compares the leaf sequences of the two input trees and returns `True` if they are identical, and `False` otherwise.
